race.comment: The $300,000 Gateway. BOOMTOWN BOSS (1) returned in good order with a strong win here before going down by the narrowest of margins at Listed level last time out. Gets the reliable Gollan/Maloney combination and should be right there at the business end. The well-related TUNED (2) (half to G3 winner and G1 placed Bruckner) has won two from three this campaign and will be at peak fitness now fourth run back. Capable of testing his rivals once again. The penny has dropped for READY TO SCHIPP (11) who has strung three wins together on the bounce and winning rider Wilson-Taylor stays in the saddle. Hard to knock winning form. BAND OF BROTHERS (3) is a last-start winner over this seven-furlong journey and shouldn't be underestimated. POSTER GIRL (8) makes some appeal despite the wide draw.
